We quote from a letter just received from Alexis Lichine, the author of ‘The Wines of France’: “in Beaujolais, the yield was comparatively small, due to excessive pre-harvest dryness. Hon. Ernest Marples was Minister of Transport in the Conserva- tive Government of Britain for over a decade. His avocations are mountain climbing and growing the best wine of Beaujolais.
